<H1 ALIGN="right">Home Page for John M. Linebarger</H1>
<P>
<H6 ALIGN="right"><I>(This page is optimized for Netscape Navigator 2.x)</I></H6>
<PRE> </PRE>
<HR><P>
I work at <!WA1><A HREF="http://www.sandia.gov">Sandia National Laboratories</A>
in the <!WA2><A HREF="http://www.cs.sandia.gov/SEL/">Synthetic Environment Lab</A>, 
doing virtual-reality visualization programming in 
<!WA3><A HREF="http://bach.cis.temple.edu/ACCU/c-links/">C/C++</A> and 
<!WA4><A HREF="http://www.sgi.com/Products/Dev_environ_ds.html">OpenGL</A> on high-end
<!WA5><A HREF="http://www.sgi.com">Silicon Graphics</A>
(SGI) workstations that have far more main memory that I do.  My professional
interests include software architecture, software engineering, 
<!WA6><A HREF="http://www.ifs.univie.ac.at/ISOO/overview.html">object-oriented</A> 
analysis, design, and programming, and enterprise data modeling.  
(In fact, I put myself through college as a data model.)  
<P>
I am pursuing a Master's degree in the  
<!WA7><A HREF="http://www.cs.unm.edu">Computer Science program</A> at the 
<!WA8><A HREF="http://www.unm.edu">University of New Mexico</A> (UNM) under Sandia's University
Part-Time (UPT) program.  UPT allows me to attend classes and study for 20 hours
a week, work part-time for 20 hours a week, and remain a full-time
Sandia employee.  What a deal!  I am scheduled to graduate in December 1997. 
A PhD in Computer Science is in my future, but so is a life ... 
<P>
I live in Cedar Crest,
<!WA9><A HREF="http://www.viva.com/nm/nmhome.html">New Mexico</A>, on a ridge at about 7100 feet 
with a great view of the east face of the
<!WA10><A HREF="http://www.gorp.com/gorp/resource/US_National_Forest/nm_cibol.HTM">Sandia mountains</A>.
I play
<!WA11><A HREF="http://www.teleport.com/~jdimick/cg.html">classical guitar</A>, 
enjoy 
<!WA12><A HREF="http://www.gorp.com/gorp/activity/hiking.htm">hiking, camping</A>, and 
<!WA13><A HREF="http://www.gorp.com/gorp/activity/paddle.htm">whitewater canoeing</A>, 
spend far more time hacking 
<!WA14><A HREF="http://sunsite.unc.edu/mdw/">Linux</A> than I should,
and only date women who run 32-bit operating systems.  
I have just started 
<!WA15><A HREF="http://users1.ee.net/wow/mountain.html">mountain biking</A> 
in order to get swimsuit-compatible for the summer.
<P>
